               <msContents>
                  <summary>Contract from Egypt, written on papyrus. Contract stipulates payment in installments and the mutual guarantee of the representatives of one of the parties. Mentions Kronion son of someone whose name begins with "Kron" and Tathmouis(?). Mentions also the month Payni (May/June). Verso has a census declaration in Greek (P.Duk.inv. 985 V)</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Dimensions of fragments are 5.9 x 5.5 cm. or smaller</note>
                     <note type="general">9 lines</note>
                     <note type="general">P.Duk.inv. 985 R was written along the fibers on the recto; written across the fibers on the verso in a different hand</note>
                     <note type="general">Upper margin of 3.5 cm. on the first fragment and lower margin of 2 cm. on the second fragment; left margin of 0.5 cm. on the second fragment</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
